                            <h2 class="card-title text-center" style="color:#2b4491">PROJECT INSTALL</h2>
                            <p class="card-text"><strong>1.</strong>  Install a apache web server as xampp php with version until 7.0 or 7.3 download <a href="https://www.apachefriends.org/es/index.html">here</a>.</p>
                            <p class="card-text"><strong>2.</strong>  After install xammp is install correctly, open a prompt command line as cmd or git bash, then go to your htdocs folder and execute this GIT command line:  <a href="https://www.apachefriends.org/es/index.html">here</a>.</p>  
                            <p class="card-text"><strong>3.</strong>  Once the project it's downloaded, run xampp panel control and start the apache server and the MySql database.</p>
                            <p class="card-text"><strong>4.</strong>  Type this url on your web browser <a href="http://localhost/phpmyadmin">http://localhost/phpmyadmin</a>.</p>
                            <p class="card-text"><strong>5.</strong>  Upload from folder database api_jobs.sql file into mysql phpmyadmin or open file api_jobs.sql and run the sql code directly into sql phpmyadmin <a href="http://localhost/phpmyadmin">http://localhost/phpmyadmin</a>.</p>
                            <p class="card-text"><strong>6.</strong>  Go to the project directory and open the project with your favorite code editor example: visual estudio code, sublime text, etc.</p>
                            <p class="card-text"><strong>7.</strong>  Go to the model directory then to the file conexion.php and write the name of the database, by default its call api_jobs</p>
                            <p class="card-text"><strong>8.</strong>  Write on your browser, the following url: http://localhost/apijobs</p>
                            <p class="card-text"><strong>9.</strong>  Once the database is conected everything should be ok. Now go to <a href="instructions"></a>. for further help please call <a href="tel:+56932243182">+56932243182</a> </p>
